verbose_text: Other ethnic factors may also potentially play a role in PK variability of monoclonal antibody therapies, including differences in lymph flow rate, volume and drainage; endocytosis; polymorphisms of the Fcgamma receptor gene and neonatal Fc receptor (FcRn) gene, and FcRn mediated recycling / clearance of immunoglobulin G (IgG); target levels and target mediated drug disposition / clearance; and immunogenicity [XREF_BIBR].
